    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-24T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="644"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.516/94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-24T21:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1921—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 25—9:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. My number 103, May 7th, 11 a.m. At the request of Guaranty Trust Minister of
                    Finance proposes to issue an order that no money remitted from the United States
                    with the exception of United States <pb facs="0792" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/>
                    money orders may be paid in Poland unless transmitted on official government
                    forms. He requests me to ascertain whether Department objects to this step,
                    which is obviously intended to create monopoly for Guaranty Trust Company.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
